<title type="html"><![CDATA[ppu register physical connection]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1337&amp;p=11636#p11636"><![CDATA[
The PPU has D0-D7+A0-A2+M2+R/W inputs, as well as a register select signal. These are connected straight to the NES CPU (except for the register select signal, which goes through a selector to be enabled only for $2000-$3FFF).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Thu Apr 06, 2006 8:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
